											<div class="et_post_meta_wrapper">
							<h1 class="entry-title">Controversial Comedy &#8216;The Interview&#8217; to Alter Kim Jong-Un Assassination</h1>

						<p class="post-meta"> by <span class="author vcard"><a href="http://geekshizzle.com/author/mj/" title="Posts by TheMac" rel="author">TheMac</a></span> | <span class="published">Aug 18, 2014</span> | <a href="http://geekshizzle.com/category/movies-and-series/" rel="category tag">Movies &amp; Series</a></p>
												</div> <!-- .et_post_meta_wrapper -->
				
					<div class="entry-content">
					<br><br><p>Well that escalated quickly! There have been many threats from North Korea and growing international safety concerns since the release of the trailer for the highly controversial comedy <a href="http://geekshizzle.com/tag/the-interview/">&#8216;The Interview</a>&#8216;. Sony initially <a href="http://geekshizzle.com/2014/06/23/north-korea-happy-seth-rogens-interview/">ignored the backlash</a> from The Centre for North Korea-U.S. Peace, but the situation was more serious than anticipated when a firm warning was sent to the United States to not release the upcoming comedy flick. A spokesman for the North Korean Foreign Ministry threatened <a href="http://geekshizzle.com/2014/06/26/north-korea-will-declare-war-u-s-kim-jong-un-assassination-plot-seth-rogens-film/">“merciless counter-measures”</a> according to reports released. The studio apparently has second thoughts about the release of the film, but some changes will be made to accommodate the <a href="http://geekshizzle.com/2014/07/10/north-korea-complains-u-n-seth-rogen-james-francos-kim-jong-un-assassination-movie/">concerns raised with the UN</a>.</p>
<p><b>Also see: <a href="http://geekshizzle.com/2014/06/12/james-franco-seth-rogen-joins-plot-kill-kim-jong-un-interview-trailer/">James Franco and Seth Rogen Joins Plot to Kill Kim Jong-Un in ‘The Interview’ Trailer</a></b></p>
<div id="attachment_33595" style="width: 610px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><a href="https://i0.wp.com/geekshizzle.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/08/the-interview-set-pic.jpg"><img aria-describedby="caption-attachment-33595" class="size-full wp-image-33595" alt="Seth Rogen and James Franco set pic courtesy of nextprojection.com" src="https://i0.wp.com/geekshizzle.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/08/the-interview-set-pic.jpg?resize=600%2C382" width="600" height="382" srcset="https://i0.wp.com/geekshizzle.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/08/the-interview-set-pic.jpg?w=600 600w, https://i0.wp.com/geekshizzle.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/08/the-interview-set-pic.jpg?resize=300%2C191 300w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px" data-recalc-dims="1" /></a><p id="caption-attachment-33595" class="wp-caption-text">Seth Rogen and James Franco set pic courtesy of <a title="http://nextprojection.com/2014/06/12/interview-trailer/" href="http://nextprojection.com/2014/06/12/interview-trailer/" target="_blank">nextprojection.com</a></p></div>
<p>The <a href="http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/sony-altering-kim-jong-assassination-725092">Hollywood Reporter</a> said the following:</p>
<blockquote><p>“Sources say the studio is digitally altering thousands of buttons worn by characters in the film — which on Aug. 8 was pushed from October to a prime Dec. 25 release — because they depict the actual hardware worn by the North Korean military to honor the country&#8217;s leader, Kim Jong Un, 31, and his late father, Kim Jong Il (showcasing military decorations would be considered blasphemous to the nuclear-armed nation).”</p></blockquote>
<p>There is also a graphic scene involving Kim Jong Un that will be removed apparently:</p>
<blockquote><p>“Sources say the studio is considering cutting a scene in which the face of Kim Jong Un (played by Randall Park) is melted off graphically in slow motion.”</p></blockquote>
<p><b>Catch all the drama for the &#8216;The Interview&#8217; <a href="http://geekshizzle.com/tag/the-interview/">HERE</a></b></p>
<div id="attachment_29205" style="width: 610px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><a href="https://i1.wp.com/geekshizzle.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/the-interview-poster.jpg"><img aria-describedby="caption-attachment-29205" class="size-full wp-image-29205" alt="&quot;The Interview&quot; poster" src="https://i1.wp.com/geekshizzle.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/the-interview-poster.jpg?resize=600%2C890" width="600" height="890" srcset="https://i1.wp.com/geekshizzle.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/the-interview-poster.jpg?w=600 600w, https://i1.wp.com/geekshizzle.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/the-interview-poster.jpg?resize=202%2C300 202w, https://i1.wp.com/geekshizzle.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/the-interview-poster.jpg?resize=404%2C600 404w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px" data-recalc-dims="1" /></a><p id="caption-attachment-29205" class="wp-caption-text">&#8220;The Interview&#8221; poster</p></div>
<p>James Franco stars as a talk show host, and <a href="http://geekshizzle.com/tag/Seth-Rogen/">Seth Rogen</a> his producer as they go to “the most dangerous country on earth” to interview the world’s most notorious dictator. What started out as a very dangerous business trip became even more hellish when they are recruited by the CIA to assist with the plans to take down the infamous leader. “Neighbors” helmer Evan Goldberg is back for another run with Rogen who also starred in the college humor comedy. Franco and Rogen are joined by Lizzy Caplan, Randall Park, and Timothy Simons.</p>
					</div> <!-- .entry-content -->
